# 📝 What is Decision Making?

Decision Making means choosing one action based on a condition.

Just like in real life:

```text
IF it rains

↓

Take Umbrella

ELSE

Do not take Umbrella
```

Programming follows the same logic.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 IF Statement

## Definition

The **IF** statement executes a block of code **only if the condition is TRUE**.

### Syntax

```text
START

INPUT Variable

IF Condition

    OUTPUT Result

STOP
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 🌍 Real-Life Example

```text
IF Traffic Signal is Green

↓

Go

Otherwise

Wait
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 Example 1 – Positive Number

## Problem

Check whether a number is positive.

### Algorithm

```text
1. Start

2. Read Number

3. If Number > 0

4. Print Positive

5. Stop
```

### Pseudocode

```text
START

INPUT Number

IF Number > 0

    OUTPUT "Positive"

STOP
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 ELSE Statement

## Definition

The **ELSE** statement executes when the **IF condition is FALSE**.

### Syntax

```text
START

INPUT Variable

IF Condition

    OUTPUT True Result

ELSE

    OUTPUT False Result

STOP
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 🌍 Real-Life Example

```text
IF Today is Sunday

↓

Play Cricket

ELSE

Study
```

Only one block will execute.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 Example 2 – Positive or Negative

### Problem

Check whether a number is Positive or Negative.

### Pseudocode

```text
START

INPUT Number

IF Number > 0

    OUTPUT "Positive"

ELSE

    OUTPUT "Negative"

STOP
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 Example 3 – Even or Odd

### Condition

```text
Number % 2 == 0
```

### Pseudocode

```text
START

INPUT Number

IF Number % 2 == 0

    OUTPUT "Even"

ELSE

    OUTPUT "Odd"

STOP
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 Example 4 – Voting Eligibility

Condition

```text
Age >= 18
```

### Pseudocode

```text
START

INPUT Age

IF Age >= 18

    OUTPUT "Eligible to Vote"

ELSE

    OUTPUT "Not Eligible"

STOP
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 Example 5 – Greater of Two Numbers

### Pseudocode

```text
START

INPUT A

INPUT B

IF A > B

    OUTPUT "A is Greater"

ELSE

    OUTPUT "B is Greater"

STOP
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 Example 6 – Pass or Fail

Condition

```text
Marks >= 35
```

### Pseudocode

```text
START

INPUT Marks

IF Marks >= 35

    OUTPUT "Pass"

ELSE

    OUTPUT "Fail"

STOP
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 💻 Java vs Pseudocode

## Pseudocode

```text
IF Marks >= 35

    OUTPUT "Pass"

ELSE

    OUTPUT "Fail"
```

↓

## Java

```java
if(marks >= 35){

    System.out.println("Pass");

}
else{

    System.out.println("Fail");

}
```

### Difference

| Pseudocode | Java |
|------------|------|
| Easy English | Programming Language |
| No Syntax Rules | Strict Syntax |
| Used for Planning | Used for Execution |

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

